He is saying, I think, that the range &quot;1200 to 3000&quot; isn't that wide.<br>
<br>
With SoS topping out at 2740, only 10% below the max possible roll from Shock of Magic, max crits from SoM aren't that impressive compared to far more common high crits from SoS.<br>
<br>
SoS's max crit is 6521 with pre-RZ drops.<br>
SoM's max crit is 7140, 9% higher than SoS's max crit.<br>
<br>
Take the top 5% of crits from SoS.  9% of SoM's crits match or exceed it, ignoring resist problems with SoM.<br>
<br>
Not what you call extremely jaw dropping numbers.<br>
<br>
In exchange, you get a spell that has an 18% worse ratio, 5% weaker DPS, 30 points easier to resist. . .<br>
<br>
Then again, I guess you don't have to use SoM.  AT out ratios it (93% of SoS's ratio), reaches 97% of the DPS, and has a 20 point resist edge over SoM.  So, you could view AT as the real magic nuke, while SoM is just there to see if you can get the highest crit number.  =)<br>
